OTO Courses FAQ

How do I learn online?
The course consists of online one-to-one sessions with a private instructor. Each session is 1 hour long. The sessions are live and aren’t recorded. The session happens through an audio call through our website with the session material shared on your screen by your instructor. The instructor is going to customize a course according to your personal needs. The whole process is done on this website.
 What do I need to attend this course?
All you need is:

- A stable internet connection with at least 2MB bandwidth
- A laptop/computer or an IOS/Android device
- A headset (Headphones + Mic)
- A relaxed quiet environment fit for learning
 How can I try your service?
You may book a trial session with a nominal fee and try for yourself. When you book a course with an instructor, you may change the instructor up to 2 times.
 Do I get a copy of the material?
Our material is on our website and the instructor will also be providing you with external material links. You have access to the material on our website for as long as you are subscribed. You do also have the right to download your recorded sessions on your computer/laptop to be reviewed anytime.
Is there a Placement Test?
Yes! There are 2 CEFR based tests:

- Basic Placement Test: This test is a quick short test that will test your listening and reading to give you a general idea of which level you are; Beginner, Intermediate or Advanced, this will guide you to pick the right course.
- In-Depth Placement Test: This test is 2 hours long and will test all your skills, reading, listening, writing and speaking as well as your grammar, you will need to do this test at the beginning of your course for your instructor to design the perfect course for your needs.
Can I book more than 8 hours per month?
Yes! You can book up to 24 hours per month. For the more committed learners, we recommend only 16 hours per month.
 Are your certificates accredited?
Our certificates are accredited by OTO Courses, and this is based on “CEFR” The Common European Framework of Reference for Languages based testing we do.
